[2023-03-09 15:10:10] [ERROR] {"type":0,"tts":false,"timestamp":"2023-03-09T09:40:10.334000+00:00","referenced_message":null,"pinned":false,"nonce":"1083323334394904576","mentions":[],"mention_roles":[],"mention_everyone":false,"member":{"roles":["859867912629911632"],"premium_since":null,"pending":false,"nick":null,"mute":false,"joined_at":"2023-02-27T03:10:02.321000+00:00","flags":0,"deaf":false,"communication_disabled_until":null,"avatar":null},"id":"1083323335401807892","flags":0,"embeds":[],"edited_timestamp":null,"content":"By now I'd say that given the wallet size you are able to handle, combined with the position size you're willing to take per trade, answers the max_open_trades. Not hyperopt. The more trades the more risk you're taking on at any given time though.\n\nIf hyperopt tells me I should use 20 trades max, but I have a $1000,- wallet with $100,- stake size, I can only do 10.\nOn the other hand it might be more effective to set the stake size to $50,- then and go for 20.\n\nThis is quite confusing thinking about it 😉","components":[],"channel_id":"702583858826051595","author":{"username":"kciredor","public_flags":0,"id":"627491426137145344","display_name":null,"discriminator":"6707","avatar_decoration":null,"avatar":"b8933cb60cdf1a4f67197aaebe0ae6c5"},"attachments":[],"guild_id":"700048804539400213"}
