[2023-03-09 22:46:04] [ERROR] {"type":0,"tts":false,"timestamp":"2023-03-09T17:16:04.671000+00:00","referenced_message":{"type":0,"tts":false,"timestamp":"2023-03-09T11:04:20.443000+00:00","pinned":false,"mentions":[],"mention_roles":[],"mention_everyone":false,"id":"1083344517094195250","flags":0,"embeds":[],"edited_timestamp":null,"content":"I'm pretty sure it's connected to FreqUI somehow. I'm not touching it since yesterday around 10pm. FT sessions are constantly at two. As soon as I open FreqUI they jump and it seems they are not closed in time anymore. Will update the issue this evening with my observations.","components":[],"channel_id":"702584313354518659","author":{"username":"smidelis","public_flags":0,"id":"319576628231667712","display_name":null,"discriminator":"1953","avatar_decoration":null,"avatar":"4a12d0bf2cf76be37138dc0cc31de6e1"},"attachments":[]},"pinned":false,"nonce":"1083438067152322560","message_reference":{"message_id":"1083344517094195250","guild_id":"700048804539400213","channel_id":"702584313354518659"},"mentions":[{"username":"smidelis","public_flags":0,"member":{"roles":["859867912629911632","824710331896299570"],"premium_since":null,"pending":false,"nick":null,"mute":false,"joined_at":"2021-10-27T22:15:55.099000+00:00","flags":0,"deaf":false,"communication_disabled_until":null,"avatar":null},"id":"319576628231667712","display_name":null,"discriminator":"1953","avatar_decoration":null,"avatar":"4a12d0bf2cf76be37138dc0cc31de6e1"}],"mention_roles":[],"mention_everyone":false,"member":{"roles":["835765504945553408","859867912629911632","702579504966795335"],"premium_since":null,"pending":false,"nick":null,"mute":false,"joined_at":"2020-04-15T18:24:01.284000+00:00","flags":2,"deaf":false,"communication_disabled_until":null,"avatar":null},"id":"1083438067806916690","flags":0,"embeds":[],"edited_timestamp":null,"content":"oh it sure is. As mentioned before - without freqUI (or something else using the API) - you won't have more than ~2-3 threads with database access (i'd have to check the actual number).\nthe API on the other hand will start new threads \"as needed\" (basically based on load / already running requests) - according to an fastAPI issue i found - up to 40 (which would mean 40 additional sessions).\n\nAs also mentioned before - i've never seen it reach more than 6-7 parallel threads (even when HEAVILY hitting the refresh button) - so my best assumption is that requests don't finish - which can happen if the load is high - or if postgres is slow to respond - causing the delay this way.","components":[],"channel_id":"702584313354518659","author":{"username":"xmatthias","public_flags":0,"id":"691298202577666099","display_name":null,"discriminator":"2871","avatar_decoration":null,"avatar":"da20c5c9cb1d9497a582937eb1eb5e83"},"attachments":[],"guild_id":"700048804539400213"}
