[2023-03-10 00:43:39] [ERROR] {"type":0,"tts":false,"timestamp":"2023-03-09T19:13:39.089000+00:00","referenced_message":null,"pinned":false,"nonce":"1083467661397983232","mentions":[],"mention_roles":[],"mention_everyone":false,"member":{"roles":["859867912629911632"],"premium_since":null,"pending":false,"nick":null,"mute":false,"joined_at":"2023-03-01T21:51:04.589000+00:00","flags":0,"deaf":false,"communication_disabled_until":null,"avatar":null},"id":"1083467656180535399","flags":0,"embeds":[],"edited_timestamp":null,"content":"Please help....I am running freqtrade using docker-compose up and I want to partially reference the content of \"exchange\": {\"ccxt_config\": } in the freqtrade configuration file at \\user_data\\config.json. The reason is that the WOOX exchange does not support the \"api_key\" field in the configuration file. The log message shows: \"freqtrade.exchange.exchange - WARNING - Async code raised an exception: TemporaryError('Could not fetch historical candle (OHLCV) data for pair BTC/USDT due to AuthenticationError. Message: woo requires \"apiKey\" credential')\" Therefore, I need to enter the exchange's \"apiKey\" and \"secret\" again in the \"ccxt_config\", which is effective. However, for security reasons, I would like to reference another file in the same directory called config-private.json, which contains this information for \"apiKey\" and \"secret\", to keep this content from appearing in the log file and protect the information. I have tried two ways: one is to use \"$ref\": \"user_data/config-private.json\" in the \"ccxt_config\", but this reference method is invalid; the other is to add --config /freqtrade/user_data/config-private.json in the docker-compose.yml help file. However, the content of \"apiKey\" and \"secret\" still appears in the log file, so it is not feasible. Therefore, please help.","components":[],"channel_id":"824719649417199646","author":{"username":"LMAN","public_flags":0,"id":"855125096820506665","display_name":