[2023-03-11 00:40:16] [ERROR] {"type":0,"tts":false,"timestamp":"2023-03-10T19:10:16.591000+00:00","referenced_message":null,"pinned":false,"nonce":"1083829193805922304","mentions":[],"mention_roles":[],"mention_everyone":false,"member":{"roles":["859867912629911632"],"premium_since":null,"pending":false,"nick":null,"mute":false,"joined_at":"2023-02-27T03:10:02.321000+00:00","flags":0,"deaf":false,"communication_disabled_until":null,"avatar":null},"id":"1083829194707968150","flags":0,"embeds":[],"edited_timestamp":null,"content":"Quite new to freqtrade, finding my way though, saw an example strategy with buy entry like this:\n- Guard condition is `dataframe['rsi'] > self.rsi.value`\n- Trigger condition is `dataframe['close'] < dataframe[self.bb_lower.value]`\n\nI feel that the trigger is wrong. Idea is: when the candle closes below the lower bollinger band it should trigger. But the way this is coded I'm quite sure that this would also fire mid signal, say you start freqtrade when both conditions are true you would enter the trade half way the signal.\n\nAm I correct or am I missing something? My assumption is the trigger should be rewritten as `qtpylib.crossed_below(dataframe['close'], dataframe[self.bb_lower.value])`\n\nWhere the latter would actually only trigger the moment it happens, meaning a trade will open if freqtrade is running, but not if you open freqtrade lateron on the signal was sticking.","components":[],"channel_id":"702584639063064586","author":{"username":"kciredor","public_flags":0,"id":"627491426137145344","display_name":null,"discriminator":"6707","avatar_decoration":null,"avatar":"b8933cb60cdf1a4f67197aaebe0ae6c5"},"attachments":[],"guild_id":"700048804539400213"}
